00:35:16.263 --> 00:35:16.584
Go ahead.

00:35:16.864 --> 00:35:18.226
Take it away.

00:35:19.426 --> 00:35:21.349
But we said, yes, we do want to keep it.

00:35:23.072 --> 00:35:28.781
He kind of took a step back and looked at us for the first time that day and said, you know what?

00:35:28.801 --> 00:35:31.065
I think you two are going to be terrific parents.

00:35:32.327 --> 00:35:34.711
And I just thought the bar must be really low, right?

00:35:34.731 --> 00:35:39.119
Because two minutes ago, it was like, do we want to kill this child in Jenny's womb?

00:35:39.639 --> 00:35:43.666
And now we're just mother and father of the year simply by

00:35:43.842 --> 00:35:52.574
accepting the fact that there was a life inside, planned by us or not, that God had knit together within Jenny's womb.

00:35:53.355 --> 00:35:57.981
And we, though, we were inconvenienced certainly from our scheduling standpoint.

00:35:58.301 --> 00:35:59.843
What did we do?

00:35:59.903 --> 00:36:10.898
We trembled knowing that there was someone coming into this world made in the image of God, therefore worthy of honor.

00:36:11.586 --> 00:36:25.103
All life, every person, your color of skin or not, where you live or not, how you think or not, how you vote or not is worthy of honor.

00:36:26.104 --> 00:36:27.947
They're sexual orientation.

00:36:28.047 --> 00:36:33.474
We are to honor people, regardless of whether or not we agree with their choices.

00:36:33.514 --> 00:36:36.878
The Bible says honor all people.

00:36:37.659 --> 00:36:38.740
Love the brotherhood.

00:36:38.760 --> 00:36:40.242
Fear God.

00:36:40.386 --> 00:36:44.011
obey the king, we are to start at honor.

00:36:44.932 --> 00:37:03.538
Honor was what he put into her hand because he knew starting out she was a child of the king, but especially as we begin to navigate the complex choices that we make within relationships in our lives, I think honor is one of the most important ingredients.

00:37:03.778 --> 00:37:12.932
Because not only did he honor her here publicly in this moment, giving her jewelry, treating her like a princess, which is, by the way, what a child of the king is.

00:37:13.353 --> 00:37:29.618
So every person you've ever dated, every person you've ever hooked up with, every person you've ever slept with, every person you've ever downloaded pornography and lusted at their image, that's someone who's a child of the king, someone who's made by God, someone who has value and worth.

00:37:29.758 --> 00:37:32.402
And I love that he here is treating her

00:37:32.642 --> 00:37:36.367
It really is beautiful, because he is not going to be the one to marry her.

00:37:36.467 --> 00:37:39.051
He's treating her like someone else's wife.

00:37:40.112 --> 00:37:43.397
And I think until you're married, that's how every girl should be treated.

00:37:43.477 --> 00:37:46.621
And when you're married, that's how every other girl should be treated.

00:37:46.661 --> 00:37:49.945
Someone else's husband, someone else's wife.

00:37:49.965 --> 00:37:54.391
So there's an honor and a deference and a respect, and he's being careful with her.

00:37:54.452 --> 00:37:59.218
He's guarding her here, guarding her heart on behalf of another.

00:37:59.298 --> 00:38:03.084
All throughout our engagement, even, that was a mentality we had in our heart.

00:38:03.104 --> 00:38:12.721
Like, I was still treating Jenny as someone else's wife and fighting to save that gift of sex, even though I was saving it for me, until I was married.

00:38:12.741 --> 00:38:15.826
The enemy would want to put that kind of in your head like, oh, you're going to be married.

00:38:15.970 --> 00:38:16.711
two weeks.

00:38:16.771 --> 00:38:19.914
It's what does it matter but to fight and to save until that moment comes.

00:38:19.934 --> 00:38:21.316
She's someone else's wife.

00:38:21.336 --> 00:38:25.701
I was fighting for future me, fighting for future her.

00:38:25.941 --> 00:38:30.686
And I think that is a beautiful example here of the way that he honors her.

00:38:30.747 --> 00:38:33.750
But then he honors her again when he goes to her home.

00:38:33.790 --> 00:38:39.757
And even though Laban sleazy, and he is, and he'll pop up again and again in Genesis.

00:38:39.777 --> 00:38:40.938
This guy's like whack-a-mole.

00:38:40.958 --> 00:38:41.679
He's relentless.

00:38:42.299 --> 00:38:44.562
Use car salesman on steroids, right?

00:38:44.994 --> 00:38:54.215
He still, the servant does, honors Laban for what he is, the man in her life until she's married to another.

00:38:54.796 --> 00:38:55.538
And so what does he do?

00:38:55.558 --> 00:38:57.422
He goes and seeks his approval.

00:38:57.482 --> 00:38:59.527
And he talks to him about it.

00:38:59.567 --> 00:39:01.010
And he not only honored

00:39:01.186 --> 00:39:12.861
Rebecca, he gave gifts to Laban representing the bridal gift that would be given to the family as a way of entering into all the customs of the day.

00:39:13.001 --> 00:39:15.504
And cultures have changed in times different.

00:39:15.524 --> 00:39:23.314
But what is not is that God wants this spirit of honor to be in our hearts as we approach relationships.

00:39:23.778 --> 00:39:28.970
This mattered to me so much when Jenny and I's courtship and whatever you want to call it.

00:39:29.031 --> 00:39:29.712
We're dating.

00:39:29.732 --> 00:39:30.775
We were moving towards.

00:39:30.795 --> 00:39:34.684
I wanted to ask her permission to marry me.

00:39:34.704 --> 00:39:35.927
I want to ask what she married me.

00:39:35.987 --> 00:39:42.162
But first, I wanted to ask her dad and just I think these old

00:39:42.466 --> 00:39:45.552
what feel old traditions are so important.

00:39:45.572 --> 00:39:51.403
Because I was saying before, I become that covering and that protecting man in your life as your husband.

00:39:51.423 --> 00:39:54.670
I want to honor that you've had a father who has been that to you.

00:39:54.690 --> 00:39:57.796
And you would say, leave out the guy I'm dating, the girl I'm dating.

00:39:57.836 --> 00:39:58.958
He doesn't have a dad.

00:40:01.824 --> 00:40:03.026
Well, then go to her mom.

00:40:03.298 --> 00:40:04.179
Go to her aunt.

00:40:04.279 --> 00:40:06.883
Go to any respected person in her life.

00:40:06.923 --> 00:40:11.790
And just honor whoever's been protecting her until you step in that place.

00:40:11.810 --> 00:40:13.713
I'm just guarantee you, God will bless that.

00:40:13.793 --> 00:40:17.338
What would you want whoever's dating your daughter one day to do?

00:40:17.378 --> 00:40:21.183
What would you want the person dating your little sister to do?

00:40:21.203 --> 00:40:25.810
How would you want him to treat her and treat that daughter of the king

00:40:25.986 --> 00:40:26.567
in that way.

00:40:26.587 --> 00:40:29.450
I'm just telling you, these things might feel like so.

00:40:29.470 --> 00:40:30.511
That is so old school.

00:40:30.531 --> 00:40:31.132
What do you want me to do?

00:40:31.152 --> 00:40:32.994
Start sending telegrams as well?

00:40:33.074 --> 00:40:34.716
I'm just saying, this stuff is amazing.

00:40:34.736 --> 00:40:41.584
And there's a reason God has put it into our hearts and start to be the change in the culture that God wants for you to be.

00:40:41.604 --> 00:40:44.888
I thought I'd get at least an amen for some girls up in here.

00:40:44.908 --> 00:40:45.548
But no, it's all right.

00:40:47.551 --> 00:40:50.514
I think that we learn from these three things.

00:40:50.626 --> 00:40:51.587
a lot of beautiful things.

00:40:51.787 --> 00:40:56.133
And how it worked out, if you look at verse 54, we're going to jump back in here now.

00:40:57.014 --> 00:41:01.319
It all worked out pretty well, because he and the men who were with him in aid and drink stayed all night.

00:41:02.200 --> 00:41:05.504
Then they arose in the morning, and he said, send me away to my master.

00:41:06.485 --> 00:41:14.775
But her brother and her mother said, let the young woman stay with us a few days, at least 10, that she may go.

00:41:15.616 --> 00:41:20.242
And he said to them, do not hinder me.

00:41:20.450 --> 00:41:24.698
Since the Lord has prospered my way, send me away so that I may go to my master."

00:41:25.519 --> 00:41:28.384
So they said, well, we will call the young women and ask her personally.

00:41:28.404 --> 00:41:33.073
Then they called Rebecca and said to her, will you go with this man?

00:41:33.113 --> 00:41:38.162
And she said, and I love this, I will go.

00:41:39.170 --> 00:41:45.820
We'll get to why exactly Laban tried to slow them down a little bit here, what exactly was going on, and why the servant didn't tolerate it.

00:41:45.860 --> 00:41:52.629
But first, let me just show you, as we approach our relationships with care, just as we begin to wind this down, four quick handles.

00:41:52.729 --> 00:41:58.578
Four handles that we can have on our approach to relationships that will help us to care for them as we should.

00:41:58.618 --> 00:41:59.739
The first is creativity.

00:42:00.761 --> 00:42:01.262
Creativity.

00:42:01.402 --> 00:42:07.090
I love that the servant was creative as he tried to figure out, is this girl a servant?

00:42:07.522 --> 00:42:11.608
You'll notice he didn't just go up to all the girls of the world and go, y'all, who's a servant here?

00:42:12.449 --> 00:42:13.971
Anybody here have a servant's heart?

00:42:15.413 --> 00:42:19.779
Because anybody can say whatever they want to when they're filling out their e-harmony profile.

00:42:19.799 --> 00:42:24.966
Anybody can say whatever when they're filling out their Christian mingle or whatever.

00:42:25.006 --> 00:42:26.248
And I'm not knocking that.

00:42:26.288 --> 00:42:29.753
I know plenty of people who have met over the internet, and God uses those things.

00:42:29.953 --> 00:42:33.458
But I'm just saying anybody can say whatever they want about what's in their heart.

00:42:33.826 --> 00:42:38.686
But these actions that we live out over time, they really do betray it.

00:42:39.047 --> 00:42:43.666
And so the servant was creative to see and to witness and to find out if it was there.

00:42:43.810 --> 00:42:44.311
What did he do?

00:42:44.351 --> 00:42:47.175
He put a situation together that would allow him to find out.

00:42:47.235 --> 00:42:51.302
If I ask for a water and you give my camel's water, too, that's the servant's heart.

00:42:51.322 --> 00:42:53.746
I'm watching you without you knowing you're being studied.

00:42:54.106 --> 00:43:09.010
And I think that's one of the most powerful reasons why it's important for us to be creative and to be careful about how we see, how we watch for opportunities during the dating phase to see what's really going on inside this person's heart.

00:43:09.218 --> 00:43:11.040
Is there really a servant's fear?

00:43:11.100 --> 00:43:17.989
I think serving within the church, serving God within your city and ministry you're doing, I think that is a powerful way to watch.

00:43:18.049 --> 00:43:20.612
How do they handle difficult situations?

00:43:20.652 --> 00:43:27.581
How do they handle having a team lead on this group of online hosts who all say, here's when you're supposed to be, or do they show up on time?

00:43:27.961 --> 00:43:29.944
What's their work ethic like?

00:43:29.984 --> 00:43:33.969
This girl had that not only servant heart, but just an amazing work ethic.

00:43:33.989 --> 00:43:35.090
And he was creative.

00:43:35.202 --> 00:43:39.028
I think creativity must be employed in really figuring out what's going on.

00:43:39.048 --> 00:43:41.492
Because listen, you can suck it in for a little while.

00:43:41.833 --> 00:43:44.237
But over time, the reality comes out.

00:43:44.297 --> 00:43:46.040
What's really there comes out.

00:43:46.100 --> 00:43:48.764
And you must not be in such a hurry or we're going to get married.

00:43:49.065 --> 00:43:50.828
You just met two minutes ago.

00:43:51.088 --> 00:43:52.971
And you're like, well, this guy did this.

00:43:53.212 --> 00:43:53.532
All right.

00:43:53.572 --> 00:43:54.594
Well, this is Abraham's.

00:43:54.614 --> 00:43:54.895
All right.

00:43:54.935 --> 00:44:01.746
So I'm just telling, in our day today, we needed to give time, give space to allow there to be

00:44:02.210 --> 00:44:08.178
opportunities to see what God has really done in their heart before we rush into a relationship with this person.

00:44:08.739 --> 00:44:22.738
Creativity is also necessary in marriage, in relationships, being creative at how you express love, being creative at how you approach date nights and connecting together and growing in your love for each other, being creative

00:44:22.818 --> 00:44:31.327
in how you approach parenting and leading a home, finding things that are fun to do with your family to really continue to grow in those friendships and relationships.

00:44:31.407 --> 00:44:33.970
Creativity is so important.

00:44:34.090 --> 00:44:38.155
Secondly, I want to talk for a second about attractions, the second handle.

00:44:38.175 --> 00:44:42.380
Because verse 16 says, Rebecca was very beautiful to behold.

00:44:43.220 --> 00:44:44.021
And that's important.

00:44:44.582 --> 00:44:45.163
Why is it there?

00:44:45.203 --> 00:44:45.963
Because it's true.

00:44:46.384 --> 00:44:48.266
And he thought she was attractive.

00:44:48.306 --> 00:44:49.908
And Isaac will find out later.

00:44:50.008 --> 00:44:51.890
He thinks that she's attractive.

00:44:52.002 --> 00:44:54.485
And I don't want to belittle the importance of that.

00:44:54.505 --> 00:44:58.428
I think it's oftentimes in the church kind of this like, oh, it doesn't really matter.

00:44:58.449 --> 00:44:59.450
That's not really that important.

00:44:59.470 --> 00:45:01.071
Hey, FYI, it is important.

00:45:01.492 --> 00:45:06.116
If you're going to be married for the rest of your life, it would be not a terrible thing to like what you see.

00:45:06.156 --> 00:45:07.858
That's not bad.

00:45:07.898 --> 00:45:09.380
That's not a bad thing at all.

00:45:09.440 --> 00:45:12.423
Chemistry and how you feel and that you like this person.

00:45:12.643 --> 00:45:14.024
But listen to me carefully.

00:45:14.144 --> 00:45:15.686
It's not the most important thing.

00:45:16.387 --> 00:45:19.730
So for him, the prerequisite was where she was from.

00:45:19.874 --> 00:45:26.383
that she's willing to come and go out of the place that she lived, that she was a servant.

00:45:26.623 --> 00:45:28.526
And then down the list is this idea.

00:45:28.946 --> 00:45:30.609
She's beautiful as well.

00:45:31.049 --> 00:45:34.674
Proverbs 31 says, charm can mislead, and beauty soon fades.

00:45:35.055 --> 00:45:40.242
But the woman to be admired and praised is the woman who lives in the fear of God.

00:45:40.578 --> 00:45:54.899
So as you're thinking through who you're going to date and who you're going to approach and who you want, think about in your head something deeper than just a superficial, something deeper than just money, something deeper than just their looks, that there's something on the inside in their soul.

00:45:55.200 --> 00:46:00.548
You think about the marriage vows, till death do us part for better or for worse, for richer or for poorer.

00:46:00.648 --> 00:46:10.002
Think about as you're choosing who you're going to make this decision to live with your soul connected to, that it's going to be someone who it would be an honor to suffer with.

00:46:10.178 --> 00:46:12.561
Someone who would be a joy to go through life with.

00:46:12.601 --> 00:46:18.468
If one of you, God forbid, ended up in a wheelchair, unemployed, or God forbid the worst happened.

00:46:18.488 --> 00:46:19.950
And someone in your home dies.

00:46:19.970 --> 00:46:28.840
And just to deal with the suffering that it would be someone who it would be just as much of a joy to walk with in lean times as in the fat times.

00:46:28.860 --> 00:46:30.182
So attraction is important.

00:46:30.222 --> 00:46:32.505
It's just not the most important thing.

00:46:33.146 --> 00:46:34.467
Then third hand, a resolve.

00:46:35.148 --> 00:46:38.772
There needs to be resolve in relationships and resolve to do what?

00:46:38.812 --> 00:46:40.114
To do God's will.

00:46:40.546 --> 00:46:41.487
to do God's will.

00:46:42.528 --> 00:46:44.531
The servant, he had asked permission.

00:46:44.911 --> 00:46:46.273
Laban gave consent.

00:46:46.393 --> 00:46:48.215
He said, I can't speak about this good or evil.

00:46:48.255 --> 00:46:51.179
It's clearly God's doing that you're here, this whole thing.

00:46:51.239 --> 00:46:53.141
Everybody recognized there in that moment.

00:46:53.161 --> 00:46:53.682
This is happening.

00:46:53.702 --> 00:46:54.363
They gave permission.

00:46:54.403 --> 00:46:54.963
You can marry her.

00:46:55.204 --> 00:46:59.829
But then when the day came for them to leave, he goes, you can leave just not yet.

00:47:00.570 --> 00:47:03.634
And he said, stay a couple of days, perhaps 10.

00:47:04.002 --> 00:47:10.052
which many commentaries suggest is actually a way in that culture of saying, up to 10 months, we'll figure it out.

00:47:10.072 --> 00:47:11.975
We'll keep talking about it as time goes on.

00:47:11.995 --> 00:47:21.711
You can go just not yet and kind of hoping that instead, Isaac would be brought back there instead of her going to be with them.

00:47:21.831 --> 00:47:30.866
And the servants saw through this for what it was, an attempt to procrastinate and eventually talk him out of God's will, which is one of the devil's most successful strategies.

00:47:30.978 --> 00:47:33.905
He won't just try and tell you not to do what God called you to do.

00:47:33.965 --> 00:47:35.830
He'll tell you to do it tomorrow.

00:47:36.130 --> 00:47:37.995
He'll tell you you can do it later.

00:47:38.296 --> 00:47:40.421
J.C. Ryle once said, and I love this quote.

00:47:40.441 --> 00:47:47.538
He said, Satan doesn't care how spiritual your intentions are as long as they are determined to be done later.

00:47:48.002 --> 00:47:50.707
Because the road to hell is paved with good intentions.

00:47:50.727 --> 00:47:56.516
And many of us have been talked out of doing the things we're called to do one day at a time, one year at a time.

00:47:56.576 --> 00:47:59.622
So the servant here, he said, I am not going to be deterred.

00:47:59.902 --> 00:48:00.603
We're going to go.

00:48:00.884 --> 00:48:01.845
You said we can go.

00:48:01.865 --> 00:48:03.949
The time to go is now.

00:48:04.289 --> 00:48:05.752
He said, do not hinder me.

00:48:05.812 --> 00:48:06.573
Send me away.

00:48:06.593 --> 00:48:07.555
So there was resolve.

00:48:07.575 --> 00:48:08.717
Do you see that in his heart?

00:48:09.037 --> 00:48:10.159
Because he knew what was at stake.

00:48:10.179 --> 00:48:14.226
And then secondly, I see in Rebecca that there was resolve.

00:48:14.690 --> 00:48:22.665
And there had been for some time, because verse 16 says, though she was very beautiful to behold, she was a virgin.

00:48:22.905 --> 00:48:27.834
And the choice that she had made led her to being at a place where no man had known her.

00:48:28.395 --> 00:48:34.246
Now clearly in that day, just like in any day, it would be easy to have compromise for her.

00:48:34.587 --> 00:48:38.674
But she's come to this moment, and she not only has this servant's heart,

00:48:38.786 --> 00:48:40.349
as a single girl.

00:48:40.609 --> 00:48:43.494
But she's also said, I want to get to my marriage.

00:48:43.534 --> 00:48:47.921
I want to get to my wedding whoever that man is whenever that day comes.

00:48:48.021 --> 00:48:56.255
And I want to have saved myself to have waited to be intimate with anybody and to go into marriage with this gift of me to give to him.

00:48:56.295 --> 00:48:59.520
And I just love that she had that kind of resolve.

00:48:59.560 --> 00:49:03.026
I told you last week, there needs to be a purposing in your heart.

00:49:03.490 --> 00:49:09.680
that you would choose to fight for, and especially when it's difficult to choose God's best for your love life.

00:49:10.261 --> 00:49:16.011
And I realize, even in saying this, there's a lot of tension, because some of you are hearing that, I wish I could do that.

00:49:16.031 --> 00:49:17.173
I already gave that away.

00:49:17.253 --> 00:49:24.946
And I think the church has overemphasized virginity as some sort of holy grail benchmark of your love for God.

00:49:24.994 --> 00:49:38.566
And we've under-recognized what it looks like to honor God after you've made mistakes that you regret or after you've been through hard things that you didn't have a say in, whether it was the sexual assault or someone molested you when you were very young.

00:49:38.606 --> 00:49:45.472
